-- Government Seeks 10% Cut in Budget Requests From Ministries, Genba Says
-- Takashi Hirokawa
-- 2010-07-26T01:16:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/government-seeks-10-cut-in-budget-requests-from-ministries-genba-says.html

          
          
             Japan’s government is seeking a 10
percent cut in budget requests made by the nation’s ministries,
said Koichiro Genba, minister for civil service reform. The
government also plans to set aside more than 1 trillion yen ($11
billion) to promote economic growth, Genba told a group of
reporters today.  
